            <text>Effect of narrowing a pipe on Re? (Assume constant rate Q): Re ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Increases (v ~ 1/d^2, Re ~ v d ~ 1/d)</option><option id="B">Decreases</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Narrowing increases turbulence risk.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Blood is ____ fluid.</text>
            <option id="A">Non-Newtonian (Viscosity varies with shear)</option><option id="B">Newtonian</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Depends on flow speed.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Maximum height of water suckable by a pump from ground is ~____ m.</text>
            <option id="A">10.3</option><option id="B">100</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
